Uses of Package
org.kawanfw.file.api.client

  • Packages that use org.kawanfw.file.api.client 
    Package Description
    org.kawanfw.file.api.client
    Provides classes and interfaces for transferring files between a Client and a Server or to call remote Java methods through an Http session.
  • Classes in org.kawanfw.file.api.client used by org.kawanfw.file.api.client 
    Class and Description
    FileSession
    Deprecated. 
    As of version 3.0, replaced by:
    • RemoteSession for session establishment and simple file upload & download.
    • RemoteFile for operations on remote files.
    RemoteFile
    An abstract representation of file and directory pathnames on a remote host.
    RemoteSession
    Main class for establishing an http session with a remote host and for executing from client side some basic operations: Get the Java version of the servlet container on the remote server.
